  "texts": [
    "Thus, [h[Y ′] ∪ Z) is a proper filter.",
    "Let Y = [h[Y ′] ∪ Z).",
    "Then clearly XR i Y and h g (Y) ⊇ Y ′.",
    "Finally, we claim that h g (Y) ⊆ Y ′.",
    "For if z ′ ∈ h g (Y), so h(z ′) ∈ [h[Y ′] ∪ Z), then there is a y ′ ∈ Y ′ and ■ i x ∈ X such that h(y ′) ∧ x ≤ h(z ′), which implies x ≤ -h(y ′) ∨ h(z ′) and hence ■ i x ≤ ■ i (-h(y ′) ∨ h(z ′)) = h(■ i (-y ′ ∨ z ′))."
